<p>Welcome to box breathing. <break time="650ms"/>  
This technique uses four equal steps to calm your mind and body. <break time="650ms"/>  
Box breathing is great for managing stress and improving focus. <break time="650ms"/>  
Today,<break time="150ms"/> you’ll learn how to use this method anywhere you need a sense of calm. <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Let’s begin. <break time="650ms"/>  
Please find a comfortable seat. <break time="650ms"/>  
Sit upright,<break time="150ms"/> with your back supported and both feet flat on the floor. <break time="650ms"/>  
Rest your hands in your lap or on your thighs. <break time="650ms"/>  
Relax your shoulders down and away from your ears. <break time="650ms"/>  
Keep your chin level and your face relaxed. <break time="650ms"/>  
If you like,<break time="150ms"/> close your eyes or soften your gaze. <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Here’s how box breathing works. <break time="650ms"/>  
You’ll breathe in for four counts. <break time="650ms"/>  
Hold your breath gently for four counts. <break time="650ms"/>  
Breathe out for four counts. <break time="650ms"/>  
Hold again for four counts. <break time="650ms"/>  
Imagine tracing the sides of a square with each step. <break time="650ms"/>  
Let’s try one round together. <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Breathe in through your nose – One – <emphasis level="moderate">slow,<break time="150ms"/> steady breath</emphasis> <break time="650ms"/>  
Hold your breath – Two – <emphasis level="moderate">gentle pause,<break time="150ms"/> no tension</emphasis> <break time="650ms"/>  
Breathe out – Three – <emphasis level="moderate">steady,<break time="150ms"/> controlled release</emphasis> <break time="650ms"/>  
Hold again – Four – <emphasis level="moderate">relaxed,<break time="150ms"/> don’t strain</emphasis> <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Pause for a moment. <break time="650ms"/>  
Notice if your body feels calm and steady. <break time="650ms"/>  
Check that your shoulders are relaxed and your breath is smooth. <break time="650ms"/>  
If you feel lightheaded,<break time="150ms"/> return to normal breathing and join in when ready. <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Now,<break time="150ms"/> let’s complete five full boxes together. <break time="650ms"/>  
Remember,<break time="150ms"/> it’s okay to adjust the count if needed. <break time="650ms"/>  
Keep your breaths smooth and even. <break time="650ms"/></p>
