<prosody rate="-5%" pitch="+10%">Four - <emphasis level="moderate">Hold,<break time="150ms"/> finish with ease</emphasis> <break time="3000ms"/></prosody></p>
<p>If holding your breath feels uncomfortable,<break time="150ms"/> shorten the hold to two counts. <break time="650ms"/>  
For more challenge,<break time="150ms"/> try six counts per side,<break time="150ms"/> but always stay relaxed. <break time="650ms"/>  
Remember, <emphasis level="strong">never force your breath or strain your body</emphasis>. <break time="650ms"/></p>
<p>Box breathing can help regulate your nervous system and sharpen your focus. <break time="650ms"/>  
It’s a practical tool for stressful situations,<break time="150ms"/> helping you stay calm and alert. <break time="650ms"/>  
With regular practice,<break time="150ms"/> you can use this technique anytime you need a reset. <break time="650ms"/>  
Great work today—keep using box breathing whenever you need a moment of calm and clarity. <break time="650ms"/></p>
